{"TopicId":119321,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Force OpenGL on Wnidows 8","CreatedByName":"SOHEIL","CreatedById":138377,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-25T13:00:49Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SOHEIL","CreatedById":138377,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-25T13:00:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EPlease tell me how can i Force OpenGL on Windows 8 !\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMy system gets out of memory \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMy system :\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECore-i7 870\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E4 GB RAM\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EZotac GT220\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eddiew","CreatedById":127483,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-25T13:10:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EShould be the same as any other version of window: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/84203-Less-memory-usage-by-using-OpenGL\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/84203-Less-memory-usage-by-using-OpenGL\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMake a shortcut\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdd \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#333333;\u0022\u003E-force-opengl to the command line of that shortcut\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#333333;\u0022\u003ELaunch with shortcut\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#333333;\u0022\u003EWatch performance drop \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#333333;\u0022\u003EBut sometimes sacrifices must be made!\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Val","CreatedById":126227,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-25T13:42:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022 data-cite=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E...\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#333333;\u0022\u003EWatch performance drop \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E...\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENot always. My system runs better with -force-opengl\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EZotac GeForce GTX 980 AMP! Omega Edition\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIntel i7-4790K CPU\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E16GB of Corsair Vengeance DDR3\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnd by \u0022running better\u0022, I mean, no fps drop and it takes many more reverts, higher parts counts and longer play times before hitching and crashes occur.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI used to have an AMD R9 290X before. And with that there was a definite fps drop and no shadows with -force-opengl.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SOHEIL","CreatedById":138377,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-25T14:45:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ethanks\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}